
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `cd-create-profile` baraye dorost kardane yek profile jadid dar system estefade mishavad. In dastoor be shoma komak mikonad ta yek profile ba setting-haye makhsoos be khodeton ijad konid.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `--name <esm>`  -->  🏷️ Esme profile jadid ra moshakhas mikonad.
    🔹 `--path <masir>` --> 📍 Masire zakhire shodan profile ra tayin mikonad (agar tayin nashavad, be soorate pishfarz zakhire mishavad).
    🔹 `--default`      -->  ⭐ Profile jadid ra be onvane profile pishfarz gharar midahad.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ cd-create-profile --name karbar1

    🔹 Yek profile ba esme "karbar1" misazad.

    $ cd-create-profile --name karbar2 --path /home/karbar2/profile

    🔹 Yek profile ba esme "karbar2" dar masire `/home/karbar2/profile` misazad.

    $ cd-create-profile --name karbar3 --default

    🔹 Yek profile ba esme "karbar3" misazad va aan ra be onvane profile pishfarz tayin mikonad.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ cd-create-profile --name test_profile

    🔹 Ba ejraye in dastoor, yek profile ba esme `test_profile` sakhte mishavad va shoma mitavanid az aan baraye setting-haye khass estefade konid. Agar masir tayin nashavad, profile dar masire pishfarz zakhire khahad shod.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `cd-create-profile` command is used to create a new profile on the system. This command helps you to create a profile with your own specific settings.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `--name <name>`  --> 🏷️ Specifies the name of the new profile.
    🔹 `--path <path>` --> 📍 Specifies the path where the profile will be saved (if not specified, it will be saved in the default location).
    🔹 `--default`      --> ⭐ Sets the new profile as the default profile.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ cd-create-profile --name user1

    🔹 Creates a profile named "user1".

    $ cd-create-profile --name user2 --path /home/user2/profile

    🔹 Creates a profile named "user2" in the path `/home/user2/profile`.

    $ cd-create-profile --name user3 --default

    🔹 Creates a profile named "user3" and sets it as the default profile.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ cd-create-profile --name test_profile

    🔹 By running this command, a profile named `test_profile` will be created and you can use it for custom settings. If the path is not specified, the profile will be saved in the default location.
